    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Oil Pan and Oil Suction Tube - Removal -
        Removing the Oil Pan
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="S2650701" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>Removing the Oil Pan</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To avoid serious personal injury, possible death, or damage to the engine or vehicle, read all
                    safety instructions in the "Safety Information" section of this manual.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To avoid serious personal injury, possible death, or damage to the engine or vehicle, make sure
                    the transmission is in neutral, parking brake is set, and wheels are blocked before doing diagnostic
                    or service procedures on engine or vehicle.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f26507remove01" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH06/H06016.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing the oil pan mounting bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 18 (M8 x 24) oil pan mounting bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f26507remove02" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH06/H06052.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing the oil pan</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift the oil pan from the engine.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f26507remove06" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH06/H06031.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px" box="no"/>
            <caption>RTV sealant locations</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Front cover (front half)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Front cover (rear half)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Gasket</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">RTV sealant locations</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankcase</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Flywheel housing</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a knife or scraper to cut through the RTV sealant under the oil pan gasket at six
                locations on the crankcase mounting surface.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f26507remove03" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH06/H06025.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing the oil pan gasket</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the oil pan gasket from the crankcase mounting surface and discard.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
